# 5. 忘れられない記憶

Airi: Okay, our schedule for the week after next seems set...
Airi: *Sigh* That took longer than I was expecting... It's getting pretty late, so I should probably go to bed soon.
Airi: Oh, but before I do, I'll go over what we're doing tomorrow one last time.
Airi: Let's see... It's another afternoon meeting, so I'll need to make sure to remind Shizuku in the morning.
Airi: (Ideally, we'd all be there to discuss what's going on...)
Airi: (Which is why Minori switching into the credit-based course would be a good thing for MORE MORE JUMP!)
Airi: (But she has to make that decision. I'm in no position to intervene.)
Airi: (Still...)
Airi: ...
Airi: *Sigh* Stop it. Thinking about that is only making your head hurt...
Airi: I feel bad always asking them for help, but I wanna talk to Miku and the others about this...
Airi: Where are Miku and...? Huh?
KAITO: That's about it... Please remember to add in breaks when you're putting a schedule together like this.
Shizuku: Thank you very much, KAITO. You've taught me so much.
KAITO: You're very welcome! Feel free to ask me again if you have any questions.
Shizuku: Yes! Oh, isn't that...?
Rin: Hey! It's Airi!
Airi: Good evening, everyone. I didn't realize you'd be here so late, Shizuku.
Airi: Were you discussing something? I hope I'm not interrupting.
Shizuku: No, you're not interrupting. They just finished helping me.
Airi: Helping you?
Rin: Shizuku was asking KAITO about how to put schedules together and stuff!
Shizuku: You've been trying to adjust our schedule because of how busy we've been with work lately, right, Airi?
Shizuku: I was hoping that I could help somehow... Which is why I came to see KAITO.
Airi: I see. So that's why...
KAITO: Mind if I ask why you're here, Airi? I assume you came here for a reason.
Airi: Actually, I was also hoping to get some help from you guys.
Airi: It involves you, Shizuku, so do you think you could stick around to listen?
Shizuku: Yes, of course.
Airi: Thanks. So...
Shizuku: I see... Minori is thinking about switching to the credit-based course.
Miku: I hope she finds an answer that she's happy with...
Airi: She seemed to be giving it a lot of serious thought, so she might need some time. But I believe she will.
Airi: At the same time...
KAITO: Is something about this bothering you, Airi?
Airi: So, um...
Airi: I know it's because I suggested using the freedom we get as credit-based students...
Airi: But now that Minori's considering it as an option... A part of me is wondering whether that's really all for the better.
Shizuku: Airi...
Airi: I thought I fully understood that I shouldn't be intervening, but I can't shake this feeling...
Luka: Yes, the credit-based course would certainly allow you to do more as MORE MORE JUMP! since you'd be able to accept more of the offers you've been receiving.
Rin: But you might end up not as close with your friends, right...?
Airi: I'm not saying that Minori's absolutely gonna go through that, but...
Airi: Minori has Shiho, Kohane and lots of other classmates that she's really close with...
Airi: I'm worried that going credit-based will prevent her from seeing them and cause a lot of pain for her. That's been bothering me...
Len: Right...
Airi: Again, I know. I probably shouldn't be saying any of this.
MEIKO: No, I understand how you feel. I mean, seeing friends drift apart is never easy.
Airi: Thanks, MEIKO.
Miku: But what's the right answer...? It seems like she has to choose between being an idol and being with her friends.
Rin: No, that's terrible... Both mean so much to her.
MEIKO: Yes. In a perfect world, she wouldn't have to sacrifice either...
KAITO: Um, Airi? You don't have to, but would you mind telling us more about how you and your friends drifted apart?
KAITO: I know it's not a happy moment in your life, but it may give us some clues as to what we can do now...
Airi: ...
Airi: Right... It's definitely not a fun story, but if you're all willing to listen...
